1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,004
<i>- Dear, I'm here. Mommy's here.</i>
<i>- It's not me Mommy.</i>

2
00:00:04,087 --> 00:00:07,549
<i>That's not me! </i>[sobs]

3
00:00:07,632 --> 00:00:09,384
[Alice] <i>We all know who did this.</i>

4
00:00:11,136 --> 00:00:12,303
[Artillero] <i>Did you do this?</i>

5
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:13,555
<i>You shouldn't have done this.</i>

6
00:00:13,638 --> 00:00:14,889
<i>This will affect your case!</i>

7
00:00:14,973 --> 00:00:16,433
[Lucas] <i>Anton! Get out here!</i>

8
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:17,767
<i>You know what you did.</i>

9
00:00:17,851 --> 00:00:20,186
<i>You practically beat Mel to death!</i>

10
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:21,479
<i>What kind of man are you?!</i>

11
00:00:21,563 --> 00:00:23,314
<i>Tell Mel she's mine.</i>

12
00:00:23,398 --> 00:00:25,483
<i>Why did you do that? I know you love Mel,</i>

13
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:28,820
<i>but what she needs right now</i>
<i>is to win her case against Anton.</i>

14
00:00:28,903 --> 00:00:31,823
<i>Whatever I felt for her, that's long over.</i>

15
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:33,658
<i>You know what</i>
<i>my Brother and I went through!</i>

16
00:00:33,742 --> 00:00:35,994
<i>That will never happen</i>
<i>again in front of me, Erica.</i>

17
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:36,995
<i>Never!</i>

18
00:00:37,078 --> 00:00:38,705
<i>After this scandal,</i>

19
00:00:38,788 --> 00:00:41,416
<i>who do you think will still love me?!</i>

20
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:43,126
<i>No one will love me anymore.</i>

21
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:46,087
[Alice] <i>Many people will still love you.</i>
<i>So many of us love you.</i>

22
00:00:47,088 --> 00:00:53,636
[theme music playing]

23
00:02:03,414 --> 00:02:05,041
[Beth] Being a woman is hard.

24
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:10,421
If this happened to a man,
a video like that coming out,

25
00:02:11,506 --> 00:02:13,174
yes, he'd be embarrassed.

26
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,136
But people would forget it quickly.

27
00:02:17,095 --> 00:02:20,932
Some would laugh,
some might even applaud him,

28
00:02:21,391 --> 00:02:24,561
and life would just go on,

29
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:26,146
like nothing happened.

30
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:32,610
But when it's a woman,
like what happened to your Aunt Mel,

31
00:02:32,694 --> 00:02:34,571
everything can fall apart,

32
00:02:35,488 --> 00:02:38,950
your reputation, your whole world…

33
00:02:39,576 --> 00:02:41,828
Even if you say it's not you,

34
00:02:43,329 --> 00:02:45,331
even if you say it's fake,

35
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:48,710
even if a man did this to you,

36
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:51,713
people will judge
you forever because of it.

37
00:02:51,796 --> 00:02:56,134
[pensive music playing]

38
00:02:56,217 --> 00:03:00,430
Ma, Aunt Mel will be okay, right?

39
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:04,017
It'll be hard.

40
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:06,853
Very hard.

41
00:03:06,936 --> 00:03:10,189
Her strength and
courage will really be tested.

42
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:12,817
But I know she'll get through it.

43
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:15,111
She'll be okay

44
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:18,656
because we won't leave her.

45
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:22,702
We'll help her get through all of this.

46
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:27,874
[pensive music continues]

47
00:03:29,459 --> 00:03:32,462
[Ryan] <i>Yes, love,</i>
<i>you lied about the watch.</i>

48
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:34,631
<i>But our daughter is smart,</i>

49
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:37,967
<i>and I'm sure she'll</i>
<i>understand why you did it.</i>

50
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:42,096
[pensive music continues]

51
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:53,608
Chloe, I need to tell you something.

52
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:57,987
[pensive music continues]

53
00:03:58,071 --> 00:03:59,948
This won't be easy…

54
00:04:01,407 --> 00:04:03,076
[music fades]

55
00:04:03,826 --> 00:04:05,495
but you need to know that--

56
00:04:05,578 --> 00:04:09,207
[school bell rings]

57
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:11,834
Go on, Ma. Keep going.

58
00:04:13,169 --> 00:04:15,630
No, it's okay.
We'll continue it next time.

59
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:17,340
Go on, get to your class.

60
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:19,384
Promise, Ma? To be continued, okay?

61
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:22,095
Alright, alright. Go on now.

62
00:04:22,178 --> 00:04:24,305
Yes, Ma. I'll go now.

63
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:29,560
[uneasy music playing]

64
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:31,938
[Alice]
She's falling apart in front of us.

65
00:04:32,647 --> 00:04:34,899
I can't even do anything to help her.

66
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:39,529
[uneasy music continues, fades]

67
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,783
The fact that you're there for her,

68
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:45,535
that you stand by her,

69
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:47,287
is already a great deal of help, you know?

70
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:49,706
She's going to need help, Scott.

71
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:54,002
Real help, like… like therapy.

72
00:04:54,085 --> 00:04:55,920
Maybe even years of it,

73
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:58,256
just to be able to feel normal again.

74
00:05:01,926 --> 00:05:03,636
Are you really okay with us leaving?

75
00:05:04,929 --> 00:05:08,641
[tender music playing]

76
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:10,643
[breathes deeply]

77
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:12,979
It'll be so much better if you stayed.

78
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:17,358
[tender music continues]

79
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:19,110
But we have no choice.

80
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:22,697
We have to protect Seth.

81
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:25,658
That's the priority.

82
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:27,577
[exhales deeply]

83
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:32,874
[tender music continues]

84
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:39,922
[inhales, exhales sharply]

85
00:05:40,631 --> 00:05:42,133
- [music fades]
- [Edward grunts]

86
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,427
Oh. Good morning, sir.

87
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:46,471
Good morning,
Mister Edward. Where are you headed?

88
00:05:46,554 --> 00:05:48,181
Oh, to my niece's.

89
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:50,892
My grandson's leaving for the airport,
so we're going to say goodbye.

90
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:52,894
Oh, okay. We'll help you.

91
00:05:52,977 --> 00:05:54,187
- Thank you.
- [officer] Okay.

92
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:56,481
[tense music swells]

93
00:05:56,564 --> 00:05:58,399
[Edward] Let's get you inside, heart.

94
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:00,234
[Edward grunts]

95
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:06,199
[tense music continues, fades]

96
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:08,659
[Seth] I'll miss you, Miss Rose.

97
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:10,536
[Rose] I will miss you too, Seth.

98
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:13,498
You're making me cry.

99
00:06:13,581 --> 00:06:15,124
[Rose sobs softly]

100
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:20,880
[unsettling music playing]

101
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:22,131
[Alice sighs heavily]

102
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:30,056
[mysterious music playing]

103
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:33,434
[inhales sharply]

104
00:06:34,393 --> 00:06:39,816
Beth and Chloe have already
said goodbye to Seth this morning.

105
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:46,572
- I'll miss you, Grandma.
- [music fades]

106
00:06:48,699 --> 00:06:53,996
[soft music playing]

107
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:04,465
Aunt Erica,
you're going to protect my mom, right?

108
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:09,554
Of course, I will.

109
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:13,307
- I promise. Okay?
- [Seth] Okay.

110
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:21,732
[music becomes somber]

111
00:07:22,775 --> 00:07:26,195
Alice will come back to you.
I'll make sure of it.

112
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:28,030
[sniffs]

113
00:07:31,325 --> 00:07:37,290
[music becomes foreboding]

114
00:07:52,930 --> 00:07:57,435
[foreboding music continues]

115
00:07:57,518 --> 00:07:59,520
[voice shaking] This can't happen!

116
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:07,445
[siren wailing]

117
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:16,621
[foreboding music continues]

118
00:08:22,418 --> 00:08:24,462
[foreboding music intensifies]

119
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:25,671
[blow lands]

120
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:34,305
[foreboding music continues]

121
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:42,146
[ominous sting, music fades]

122
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:52,281
[sniffles]

123
00:08:53,407 --> 00:08:55,201
I'll come back as soon as I can.

124
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:58,704
Promise me, you'll take care of yourself.

125
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:02,333
[somber music playing]

126
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:04,627
[Scott inhales deeply] I'm serious.

127
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:07,296
I promise.

128
00:09:19,809 --> 00:09:20,893
[smooches]

129
00:09:20,977 --> 00:09:25,856
[somber music continues]

130
00:09:30,486 --> 00:09:31,779
[Seth] Mommy…

131
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:35,116
Come with us, please.

132
00:09:35,866 --> 00:09:39,328
I don't want the bad man to get you.

133
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:40,705
Please.

134
00:09:40,788 --> 00:09:42,164
[Seth sobs]

135
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:45,626
Baby…

136
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:48,796
Remember what you and Mommy talked about?

137
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:51,173
Mommy has to stay here first.

138
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:53,676
But the bad man…

139
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:55,428
Shh. No, no, no.

140
00:09:57,221 --> 00:09:59,599
I won't let the bad man get me.

141
00:10:00,474 --> 00:10:02,143
I won't let that happen.

142
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:03,644
I promise.

143
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:09,066
I love you so, so much. Okay?

144
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:11,152
I love you too, Mommy.

145
00:10:14,113 --> 00:10:15,489
[exhales deeply]

146
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:20,077
Bud…

147
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:22,413
We have to go, okay?

148
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:25,291
Okay.

149
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:27,168
Seth,

150
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:29,295
this is from aunty Althea.

151
00:10:29,378 --> 00:10:32,590
She can't come
because she has exams today.

152
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:37,219
I talked to her last night on the phone.

153
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:40,348
I'm going to miss her. [sobs]

154
00:10:40,431 --> 00:10:42,642
I'm going to miss everyone.

155
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:43,768
[Seth sniffles]

156
00:10:43,851 --> 00:10:45,770
We're going to miss you, too.

157
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:47,688
[chuckles softly]

158
00:10:48,939 --> 00:10:50,900
[sobbing]

159
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:52,943
Take care, okay?

160
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:55,446
[Seth sniffles]

161
00:10:57,156 --> 00:10:58,407
Time to go, bud.

162
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:00,201
[Seth sniffles]

163
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:06,248
[uneasy music playing, swells]

164
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:28,229
- [uneasy music continues]
- [heart beat racing]

165
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:32,024
[sobs]

166
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:38,656
[sinister music sting]

167
00:11:38,739 --> 00:11:43,202
[sinister music playing]

168
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:58,843
<i>My gosh, Susan! You're so stingy!</i>

169
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:02,888
<i>Wait here, dear. Mom is going to pay.</i>

170
00:12:04,014 --> 00:12:09,270
[sinister music continues]

171
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:30,791
[sinister music continues]

172
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,261
<i>- Oh!</i>
<i>- Oh! Sorry! I'm sorry, miss.</i>

173
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:44,430
[Susan] <i>My gosh.</i>

174
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:51,061
<i>Come. Let's go over here.</i>

175
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:53,606
<i>Thank you.</i>

176
00:12:54,231 --> 00:12:55,524
<i>Alice, come on.</i>

177
00:12:56,817 --> 00:12:57,860
<i>Alice!</i>

178
00:12:58,736 --> 00:12:59,904
[Susan] <i>Alice?</i>

179
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:02,072
<i>Alice!</i>

180
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:04,033
<i>Alice, dear!</i>

181
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:09,371
[sinister music continues]

182
00:13:12,791 --> 00:13:13,709
[exhales heavily]

183
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:15,961
[music fades]

184
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:18,047
- Alice.
- [sighs heavily] Yeah.

185
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:19,256
Are you okay?

186
00:13:20,299 --> 00:13:21,800
I don't have a choice.

187
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:26,514
At least, my son and my husband are safe.

188
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:29,767
It's one less thing to worry about.

189
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,060
That's all I want.

190
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:34,647
And what I want, what we want…

191
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:37,316
is for you to be safe, too.

192
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:40,402
Alice, don't forget
to take care of yourself.

193
00:13:40,819 --> 00:13:41,862
I won't.

194
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,784
I still need to return to my family.

195
00:13:49,453 --> 00:13:56,210
[unsettling music swells, fades]

196
00:13:56,961 --> 00:13:59,004
[dark music playing]

197
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:00,589
"She's good at riding.
Mel, let me try it, too."

198
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:01,966
- "Liar, liar, Mel's on fire!"
- "Preaching about

199
00:14:02,049 --> 00:14:04,843
female empowerment,
but this is what she does?

200
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:07,054
- Girl, you are done!"
- "She's fit for Babemax.

201
00:14:07,137 --> 00:14:08,514
#newcareer!"

202
00:14:08,597 --> 00:14:09,974
"Comment section
didn't pass the vibe check."

203
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:12,184
"Can't believe people
are still blaming the victim."

204
00:14:12,268 --> 00:14:15,938
[dark music continues, fades]

205
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:20,734
It'd be better if
you don't read the comments.

206
00:14:20,818 --> 00:14:22,403
[sniffles, exhales deeply]

207
00:14:22,486 --> 00:14:24,738
People are just laughing at what happened.

208
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:28,242
But my daughter can't even function

209
00:14:28,325 --> 00:14:30,536
because of embarrassment and fear.

210
00:14:31,036 --> 00:14:32,705
How can they do that?

211
00:14:32,788 --> 00:14:34,498
She's so broken.

212
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,501
How will she recover after this?

213
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:41,338
[sighs] I don't know what else I can do.

214
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:42,965
I'm her mom,

215
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:45,676
and I don't know what to do.

216
00:14:46,635 --> 00:14:47,720
[whimpers]

217
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:50,848
[Erica] Some people,

218
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:53,893
are capable of
doing cruel things to others.

219
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,939
That's what I've
learned in my line of work.

220
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:03,611
How do you still
see the good in all of it?

221
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:07,656
[melancholic music playing]

222
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:08,699
For me…

223
00:15:10,784 --> 00:15:13,120
I am just trying to be a good person.

224
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:16,665
The change I want to see in other people,

225
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,542
I start it with myself.

226
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:22,880
Even if I can't see it around me,

227
00:15:24,632 --> 00:15:26,133
I'll still try to.

228
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:31,430
You can do the opposite of what they want.

229
00:15:33,057 --> 00:15:36,101
If they expect you to be discouraged,

230
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:38,187
don't be discouraged.

231
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:42,316
If they want you to stay a certain way,

232
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:44,777
don't let it happen.

233
00:15:45,986 --> 00:15:47,237
Be different.

234
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:55,037
[melancholic music continues]

235
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,748
[Erica] <i>I've learned</i>
<i>that from what they did to you, Louisa.</i>

236
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:01,710
They got to decide
who they wanted you to be

237
00:16:01,794 --> 00:16:03,754
and what they wanted to see from you.

238
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:07,508
So you couldn't do anything but…

239
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:10,260
to live based on their expectations.

240
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:13,722
But you still lost in the end.

241
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:19,687
[melancholic music continues]

242
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:21,563
I made a promise to myself.

243
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:24,942
I did everything I could

244
00:16:25,025 --> 00:16:26,735
to prevent that from happening to me.

245
00:16:28,862 --> 00:16:31,323
Is that why people say I'm cold?

246
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:33,701
That I'm alone in life?

247
00:16:35,327 --> 00:16:37,830
But I know how to protect myself.

248
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:40,499
Isn't that more important?

249
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:45,587
[melancholic music continues]

250
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:58,434
[Mel] Did you feel this way when,

251
00:16:59,226 --> 00:17:01,395
Kyle spread that lie about you to Amurao?

252
00:17:12,448 --> 00:17:15,367
I didn't do anything wrong, Louisa.

253
00:17:16,952 --> 00:17:20,622
But I feel so small.

254
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,501
I feel dirty.

255
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:29,173
I just want to disappear.

256
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:33,927
How did you do it?

257
00:17:35,929 --> 00:17:37,389
How did you survive?

258
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:41,769
[sighs]

259
00:17:44,521 --> 00:17:46,065
[sighs sharply]

260
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:47,608
You know how?

261
00:17:47,691 --> 00:17:50,360
[music becomes gentle]

262
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:51,612
Because of all of you.

263
00:17:52,988 --> 00:17:58,827
You, Alice, Beth, and Erica.

264
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:02,414
You all gave me the courage

265
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:05,292
to face those judgmental people in Amurao.

266
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:07,961
[gentle music continues]

267
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:10,297
But it's different now. [sobs]

268
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:11,882
We're different.

269
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,344
Then change it again.

270
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:17,596
Start again.

271
00:18:18,806 --> 00:18:20,224
That's possible, right?

272
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:28,232
I worked so hard to get to where I am now.

273
00:18:29,274 --> 00:18:31,693
To get everything I want.

274
00:18:33,153 --> 00:18:36,532
I can't just let everything get ruined.

275
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:38,700
So what if everything gets ruined?

276
00:18:39,284 --> 00:18:40,702
Then so be it.

277
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:46,166
If you're miserable
and everything is a lie…

278
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:49,962
there's no point in holding on to it.

279
00:18:53,006 --> 00:18:54,091
Mel.

280
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:55,926
You're still breathing.

281
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:59,263
You can start again.

282
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:03,517
Not everyone gets the chance to do that.

283
00:19:04,977 --> 00:19:10,899
[gentle music continues]

284
00:19:16,238 --> 00:19:17,239
[breathes sharply]

285
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:25,539
[breath quivering]

286
00:19:28,542 --> 00:19:33,755
[gentle music continues]

287
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:40,345
[crying]

288
00:19:48,770 --> 00:19:54,526
[gentle music continues]

289
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:11,501
[music fades]

290
00:20:16,298 --> 00:20:21,303
[suspenseful music playing]

291
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:47,829
[suspenseful music continues]

292
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:57,172
[phone buzzing]

293
00:20:58,340 --> 00:20:59,591
- Hello?
- [music fades]

294
00:21:11,395 --> 00:21:12,854
About everything I said…

295
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:15,315
You had your reason to say all of that.

296
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:22,114
I still think what you did to Anton wrong.

297
00:21:23,448 --> 00:21:24,783
But I understand it.

298
00:21:26,827 --> 00:21:29,830
I reconnected with
Mel several years ago…

299
00:21:34,084 --> 00:21:36,086
because I wanted her to confess…

300
00:21:36,169 --> 00:21:37,587
[uneasy music playing]

301
00:21:37,671 --> 00:21:41,717
…that you all lied about the watch

302
00:21:42,592 --> 00:21:44,303
and sent my brother to jail.

303
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:47,556
But it all changed…

304
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:52,394
when I found out what
she was going through with Anton.

305
00:21:52,477 --> 00:21:54,938
[music becomes solemn]

306
00:21:55,022 --> 00:21:56,773
I wanted to protect her…

307
00:21:58,025 --> 00:22:00,277
because I wasn't
able to do that for my mom.

308
00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:04,489
I mistook my concern for love.

309
00:22:04,573 --> 00:22:08,118
[morose music playing]

310
00:22:08,201 --> 00:22:09,703
You don't have to explain.

311
00:22:09,786 --> 00:22:10,829
But I want to.

312
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:15,083
I want to make
everything clear for all of us.

313
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:20,839
[Mel] <i>I heard Lucas say that</i>
<i>he didn't have feelings for me anymore!</i>

314
00:22:20,922 --> 00:22:22,507
<i>That it's over between us.</i>

315
00:22:22,591 --> 00:22:24,217
<i>He wouldn't have said that</i>

316
00:22:24,301 --> 00:22:26,386
<i>if you hadn't entered the picture!</i>

317
00:22:26,470 --> 00:22:29,056
<i>Lucas is the only one who gets me!</i>

318
00:22:29,639 --> 00:22:32,601
<i>He's the only one who will accept me.</i>

319
00:22:32,684 --> 00:22:35,604
[sobs] <i>He's the only one</i>
<i>who'll love and accept me,</i>

320
00:22:35,687 --> 00:22:38,982
<i>and yet you want</i>
<i>to take him away from me, Erica!</i>

321
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:44,112
[solemn music continues]

322
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:48,116
[phone chimes]

323
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:52,704
[solemn music continues]

324
00:22:59,252 --> 00:23:03,048
<i>I'm sure by now you've seen the video</i>

325
00:23:03,131 --> 00:23:05,133
<i>that's been circulating online.</i>

326
00:23:06,093 --> 00:23:07,135
<i>Yes.</i>

327
00:23:07,761 --> 00:23:09,137
<i>With my face.</i>

328
00:23:09,846 --> 00:23:11,473
<i>But that's not me.</i>

329
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:15,519
<i>It's not me.</i>

330
00:23:16,019 --> 00:23:20,273
<i>And I know whatever</i>
<i>I say now won't even matter</i>

331
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:25,195
<i>because, you'll believe</i>
<i>whatever you want to believe.</i>

332
00:23:26,655 --> 00:23:28,782
<i>Lately, I've been feeling so exposed.</i>

333
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:32,077
<i>I feel like I'm being skinned alive,</i>

334
00:23:33,078 --> 00:23:37,124
<i>and it has made me</i>
<i>feel naked and vulnerable.</i>

335
00:23:37,207 --> 00:23:39,126
[music becomes tense]

336
00:23:39,209 --> 00:23:43,338
<i>I worked so hard for</i>
<i>everything that I have right now.</i>

337
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:45,507
<i>For who I am.</i>

338
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:48,969
<i>I did everything I could to protect it.</i>

339
00:23:49,719 --> 00:23:52,514
<i>Everything I did since then,</i>

340
00:23:52,597 --> 00:23:56,184
<i>I did to protect</i>
<i>what I thought defined me.</i> [sobs]

341
00:23:56,726 --> 00:24:00,856
<i>But I realized</i>
<i>that the things I've been protecting</i>

342
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:03,650
<i>became my own prison.</i>

343
00:24:05,819 --> 00:24:10,448
[breath quivers]<i> I'm so</i>
<i>goddamn tired of being scared.</i>

344
00:24:10,532 --> 00:24:12,492
[Mel sobbing]

345
00:24:12,576 --> 00:24:15,453
<i>So, I'm going to do</i>
<i>what my friend told me to do.</i>

346
00:24:16,663 --> 00:24:20,542
<i>You all want me to get exposed anyway.</i>

347
00:24:21,418 --> 00:24:24,546
<i>So let me finally expose the truth.</i>

348
00:24:25,088 --> 00:24:29,467
<i>I've been holding on to these</i>
<i>videos for quite some time now.</i>

349
00:24:30,135 --> 00:24:33,388
<i>But now I'm brave</i>
<i>enough to show all of you.</i>

350
00:24:33,847 --> 00:24:36,683
<i>Now I can finally set these videos</i>

351
00:24:37,392 --> 00:24:40,061
<i>and myself free.</i>

352
00:24:41,104 --> 00:24:45,483
[tense music continues]

353
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:47,194
[Mel] <i>Let go of me! Asshole!</i>

354
00:24:47,277 --> 00:24:48,737
- [blow lands]
<i>- Aah!</i>

355
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:50,530
<i>Aah! Aah!</i>

356
00:24:50,614 --> 00:24:53,325
[Anton]
<i>If you don't want to get hurt, shut up!</i>

357
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:55,827
<i>No! No!</i>

358
00:24:55,911 --> 00:24:57,537
<i>Aah! Help!</i>

359
00:24:58,205 --> 00:24:59,080
<i>Agh!</i>

360
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:00,540
<i>Help!</i>

361
00:25:00,624 --> 00:25:04,461
[tense music continues]

362
00:25:11,551 --> 00:25:14,304
<i>I reconnected with Mel several years ago</i>

363
00:25:14,387 --> 00:25:16,806
<i>because I wanted</i>
<i>her to confess that you all lied.</i>

364
00:25:16,890 --> 00:25:18,433
<i>But things changed when I found out</i>

365
00:25:18,516 --> 00:25:20,060
<i>what she was going through with Anton.</i>

366
00:25:20,143 --> 00:25:22,687
<i>I'm Anton Montenegro!</i>
<i>None of you can destroy me!</i>

367
00:25:22,771 --> 00:25:26,024
<i>Anton expects me to break, so I will not.</i>

368
00:25:26,107 --> 00:25:27,901
<i>We're here for you. We got you.</i>

369
00:25:27,984 --> 00:25:32,155
[suspenseful music playing]

370
00:25:32,239 --> 00:25:34,282
<i>You all think you can outsmart me?</i>

371
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:37,661
<i>No one is escaping. Not one of you.</i>
